title: For Sale:  Colt King Cobra - Rare Blue with original box
postcontent: Up for sale is a King Cobra, with original labeled box,  357 magnum,4 inch revolver, with Colt’s signature bright and highly-polished deep royal blued finish with original Pachmayer combat grippers and gold Colt medallions. This King Cobra has a heavy-duty barrel and as a first for Colt, a Cobra head was part of the barrel stamp breaking with the tradition of having only the name and caliber stamped on the barrel. It also has a full barrel length cylinder ejection rod protection shroud, and a thick solid rib on top of the barrel. The King Cobra's sighting system consists of a fixed iron red insert front sight and a fully adjustable iron white outline rear sight. This King Cobra was manufactured in 1989, two years after Colt first introduced the blue finish. Most of the King Cobra's you see today have a stainless steel finish, not this one. Unique to this revolver was that the King Cobra was a first in the gun business, in that it was the first time a new model of revolver was introduced in stainless steel before a blued version. The King Cobra is in very good condition. It has a mark that mirrors the top grip line however it is under the grip and two small blemished near the left trigger guard.  It also has a slight turn line. The finish is original as are all the components. Buyer pays $50.00 shipping and tranfer to a FFL required. Thanks for looking.
